@page "/ProjectMyWebsite"
<PageTitle>My Website</PageTitle>

<h3>My Games Database</h3>
<br>
I work on this website for fun and it has been a great opportunity to increase my confidence with HTML and ASP.NET.
<p>On the frontend I have a list of entries which can be sorted, edited and deleted by the user. The user can also create new entries using a form.
    This is then commited to an SQL Server database so entries are saved when the program is closed.
</p>

